import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the dataset?')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    plt.bar(data['name'], data['height'])
    plt.axhline(avg_height, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average height of individuals in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    names = data['name'].values
    text = ' '.join(names)
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', colormap='viridis').generate(text)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['age'], data['height'])
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between age and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Create a stacked histogram of age by height
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', hue='height', multiple='stack', bins=10, palette='viridis')
    
    plt.title('What is the age distribution for individuals of different heights in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='Height', loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data) # data already contains the data to be plotted. Always include this line. DO NOT modify the rest of the code template.
